Can someone explain to me what "got my heel crushing the snake" means?

The phrase "got my heel crushing the snake" is a metaphorical expression. It's often used to symbolize overcoming or defeating evil, temptation, or adversarial challenges. This imagery is deeply rooted in various cultural and religious traditions.

One of the most well-known origins of this metaphor comes from the Christian Biblical story of Adam and Eve in the Book of Genesis. After the serpent (often interpreted as Satan or a representation of evil) tempts Eve to eat the forbidden fruit, God curses the serpent, saying, "He will crush your head, and you will strike his heel." This is commonly interpreted as a prophecy about the coming of Christ and the defeat of evil.

In a more general sense, the image of crushing a snake under one's heel has come to represent the act of conquering or subduing something harmful or malevolent. It implies a struggle or conflict where the person (symbolized by the heel) ultimately triumphs over a negative force (symbolized by the snake).

When someone says they "got my heel crushing the snake," they're likely expressing their determination to overcome a challenge or obstacle they perceive as negative, harmful, or evil. It's a statement of strength, resilience, and victory against adversity.

I'm so glad this video is blowing up. Good cinematics make me feel good about playing the game, but a great cinematic like this brings me to tears & keeps me up all night.
This resonates so much with the people who have at least once struggled with mental health issues & self destructive thoughts. Many of us still remember that one time we wake up & suddenly have to search for the will to live, to keep on existing. The recurring fear of one day becoming old & indifferent, leaving our dreams forsaken. I'm made to sympathize with these characters in ways I didn't think was possible.
"Still here" is a powerful message, with the song and the animation synchronized masterfully. I absolutely love the spotlight on Kindred, my fav champion. Despite being the incarnation of death, their story is one that truly celebrates life & living.
"The only true death is to never live"

For those who don't know.
Tryndamere's immortality comes directly from Aatrox's blood magic.
How did he get aatrox blood?

@@stickfightx4489 In the lore, Aatrox goes on killing sprees for blood since he's basically nerfed in the lore (Different topic for a different day).
He went to the Freljord and killed young Tryndamere's tribe.
Filled with rage, Tryndamere charged at Aatrox, but was swatted away. As he lay on the verge of death, Aatrox imbued him with Darkin blood magic. He did this presumably so that he could be his strongest future host.
@@norionwinter7312 hhhhh now I want to know what  the first story is about XD

@@stickfightx4489 So The Darkin were once (sort of still are) God warriors from ancient Shurima.
But that also is a story for another day lol.
When the god warriors started using Blood magic, they basically were Even more powerful than before and the Aspects were forced to step in and do something about the matter.
They ended up trapping The Darkin inside of their own weapons, basically nerfing them.
Even then, Aatrox was able to kill the Aspect of War.
So basically now they need a host so they can take shape, but it will never bee the same as them having their own original form.
The story of how the Darkin came to be is REALLY good and I highly suggest watching a video from Necrit on youtube.

I love how Kindred was shown as a true entity, but then was revealed as what she is. Not death hunting you down, but the concept of imminent death.
Tryndamere wasn't fighting the Wolf and the Lamb. He was fighting the enemies attacking him, with each of their strikes being deadly. He wasn't blocking the wolf, he was blocking their attacks.
The Lamb was there because despite all his efforts, he would still have died from the 2 guys from behind. But the moment Ashe came into his help, the Lamb disappeared, because Tryndamere wasn't anymore risking to die.

I would love Kindred to be reworked into this concept. Instead of being a hunter collecting lifes, she should be the concept of imminent death. She should have an Evelynn's like passive that gives her cammuflage and increased movement speed when moving towards targets on low health

I love the symbolism in Tryndamere fighting Kindred. the fact that they are there means he is fated to die in his fight against the barbarians, but he rages against the inevitable literally fighting death itself to buy a few more precious seconds to change his fate. And when Ashe's arrows come streaking through the fog slaying the two barbarians at his back removing the thing that was fated to kill him, Kindred fades away because it's no longer his time to die. Plus the sequence itself was a pure masterpiece, Wolf's ferocity was absolutely incredible to watch and Lamb was beautiful in her grace. And you can tell Lamb was fascinated by this mortal who refused to die, not fleeing or accepting his death but defying it. Just chef's kiss incredible. Did more for Tryndamere's character than anything else Rito have ever done

My favorite thing is... Lamb tilts her head at Trynd when he almost cut her. She almost looks- curious, expectant. I like to think Kindred knew, at that point, that they were not taking him- but Lamb had to do her duty- and so she tested if that was true- could he fight until then? Would he escape Death?

I also see an uncanny parallel between Ashe and Trynd and Lamb and Wolf...

I like to think that Trynd was fighting the soldiers at the beginning but when he entered rage mode he started actually seeing Kindrid in the fight instead and immediately went to attack Lamb, thus her head tilt of curiosity.

lore wise, i can imagine that its partly because lamb is curious, confused as to why this man still chose to fight against her and wolf. why he fought so hard against a peaceful death at her arrow, instead choosing to pit himself against wolf's claws and teeth. and then, in that moment before she was going to loose her arrow and strike him down, symbolising that he had accepted his death, she lowers her bow with ashe's arrival, perhaps finally understanding.

I have a theory: The tryndamere is not really fighting against the kindreds... At the beginning of the video it shows him surrounded by several enemy soldiers and at the end of the video when Ashe kills the last two soldiers from that group that was surrounding the trynda while he was on the ground, when ashe kills the last two soldiers, it shows her looking at him and him looking at her more calmly and after that he shows several soldiers on the ground lying down, implying that trynda killed all the soldiers in a fight, more like he killed the soldiers if he was fighting the kindreds? Well, he wasn't fighting the kindreds, he was actually fighting the soldiers who were representing the kindreds. His fight against the kindreds was all a representation of the fight against all the soldiers and at the moment when Ashe kills the last two soldiers, the kindred that was being represented by all of them (soldiers) in the form of death, because the soldiers wanted to kill trynda, so kindred had to leave, as ashe ended the death threat by killing the last two soldiers. It was a great fight but it didn't really happen, he was fighting against every soldier, more for him the trynda, it seemed like it was against the kindreds only he could see the kindreds, but in reality it was the soldiers.

Never played the game, but this popped up on my main page. I have zero regrets watching it. I liked the Archangel fight against the demon in the beginning.

Morgana and Kayle facing down Aatrox.

Interestingly while he looks exactly like a demon, he’s more like a fallen god twisted by abuse of blood magic. Demons are something else entirely in this setting.

Keeping with the theme
of Death running through this cinematic, Aatrox wants nothing more than to die. But he can’t. He is bound to his sword, and neither can be destroyed by anything but a great deity.

Kayle and Morgana are two halves of an Aspect, effectively a celestial demigod based on a concept that inhabits a mortal vessel. In this case the Aspect of Justice split in half.
But they cannot destroy Aatrox, only his vessel/body.

The twins have long since split over a terrible mistake that killed their father and brought a city to ruin, Kayle, the light half chasing divinity and absolute justice, Morgana the dark half rejecting it, instead holding onto her humanity and advocating punishment and redemption as Justice.

Riot Vanguard only runs when you’re playing the game and stops running when you exit the game2. It also respects your privacy and data, and you can find more details about what data it uses and collects here1.

Riot Vanguard is necessary to prevent cheating and hacking in League of Legends, especially after the security breach in early 20233. It also ensures that all players have a fair and enjoyable gaming experience. If you want to play League of Legends again, you will need to enable Riot Vanguard on your computer. You can find more information on how to do that here3. If you have any issues or questions, you can contact Riot Games’ support team here1.

I like the subtle tilt of Lamb's head at 3:30 . She doesn't have facial expressions and this short moment of bewilderment and curiosity is basically the only emotion she shows. It's a great contrast to how ferocious Wolf is.

@@ludo_narrIt really fits their character since Death is still an unknown concept. I mean yea, beeing dead is beeing dead but how does it feel? Is there something after it? Is it just like sleeping? Who knows?

For me, all those unsolvable questions are the curiosity of the lamb while the reality that Death is the end of all living things can be seen as the Wolf.

Man, I love Kindreds concept of Death

@@nicz7694 They have these compelling opposite extreme personalities.

Wolf is all emotion and impulse. He doesn't plan ahead for his attacks. He just goes in full frontal assault. Meanwhile Lamb is the rational mind. She takes her time and only attacks when Tryn is distracted.

Lamb doesn't bother to provide cover for her partner, because she knows he isn't in any danger. Wolf on the other hand doesn't hesitate for a second to jump between Lamb and Tryn. It just doesn't cross his mind that she can't actually be harmed or killed. He just cares about her.

I loved it, but wanted a bit more. As per lore (read the story 3 years ago, hopefully it didn't change), wolf is the "coward's death", killing those who run from battle (I guess those who died while running away), while sheep is the death of those who fight till the end. So in a way, it would be nice to see them "not" fight together.

This fight, in this sense, was an in-game one; everyone fights. Also, while liking Ashe's save, it would have been nice if after she came, she would have found Trynda dead. Meaning he ulted, so the fight with kindred was those 5 seconds of invincibility his ult gives him, after which he dies. Imagine this: every time he uses his ultimate, he actually fights kindred. Amazing.

@@radubarbuceanu8466 If I remember correctly, Lamb delivers a swift death to those who accept their fate and Wolf delivers a violent death to those who try to defy death.

My interpretation is that Tryn standing up with his sword and facing Lamb was him challenging death, which is Wolf's cue to tear him apart.

6.5/10

Red eyed trynda (in his ult) on the verge of death but defying it by fighting kindred that came to collect and then the transition to ashe shooting her arrows to save him, while his eyes turn back to their normal color. Hakkını vererek bu oyunun filmini çıkarabilecek, dizisini yapabilecek de yine kendilerinden başka kimse değil. Riot çok özel bir yerde gerçekten bu tarz işler konusunda. Opiniones obtenidas tras ver la exposición de carteles



Una mujer de unos 60 años contó que un médico le sugirió a su esposo que se sometiera a un trasplante de órganos.

Una mujer de unos 60 años contó la historia de un médico que le había sugerido a su esposo que se sometiera a un trasplante de órganos hacía seis años. Si la operación se realizaba en una semana, le costaría 20 millones de yenes yendo al extranjero. Si podía esperar seis meses, sólo costaría 6 millones de yenes y podría hacerse en Japón. Para entonces, su esposo no quería utilizar el órgano de otra persona para prolongar su vida y no se operó. "En aquel momento, no pensé en absoluto en el donante de órganos. Aunque lo lamento por mi esposo, al ver estas obras hoy, me alegro mucho de que no se sometiera a una operación de trasplante en aquel momento", afirma.



La Sra. Den Kazumi.

La Sra. Den Kazumi dijo conmocionada que había oído hablar de la sustracción de órganos en vivo, pero que no sabía por qué ni cómo ocurría. Ahora había atado cabos y dijo: "Sé que muchos practicantes de Falun Gong han sido detenidos, pero ¿hay algunos que fueron detenidos para la sustracción de órganos?".

Dijo que el cartel La cosecha - Sangre y codicia mostraba que para algunas personas el dinero pesa más que un corazón y un hígado.

"Un órgano puede ser necesario para una persona que lucha por vivir, pero si sabe lo que ha pasado, ¿habría ánimo para un trasplante?", preguntó.



Estudiante universitario Yamaoka (derecha).

Antes de ver la exposición de carteles, el estudiante universitario Yamaoka no estaba seguro de poder decir que no si uno de sus familiares u otra persona cercana pudiera beneficiarse de un trasplante de órganos. "No tenía confianza para decir que no", afirma. "Sin embargo, ahora que me he enterado de las víctimas que hay detrás del trasplante de órganos para salvar vidas [que el PCCh sustrae órganos de practicantes vivos de Falun Gong], tengo la confianza para decir ¡absolutamente no!".

But Trynda's resistance to death surprised her, she was like, "um? this man seems different", the action of tilting her head to the side, showed her curiosity of this man without saying anything. Then when she about to end Trynda (represented by two enemy attacks from the back), she lowered down her arch by sensing Ash's arrows flying by. This action and her later fade-away, with Ash's appearence, was like a response to Kindred's curiosity before, "Death may come, but not today".

In this cinematic there is a few things I realized on Kindred's part. Tryndamere first sees Kindred, the death itself and they come together. I think that was enough to point out it wouldn't be that easy for Kindred because Wolf hunts the ones who want to run away whereas Lamb hunts the ones who accept their death. This man not only denied his death, he fought it. That's why they attack together. Also he could damage Kindred after his eyes turned red showing he was not going to lose. Another thing related to that is as Kindred first shot an arrow Tryndamere sliced it but after his eyes were red he punched.

All the things considered that was my favorite part in the cinematic.

pitch for a new tryndamere ult:
The Undying; passive - upon reaching 0 hp, enter the kindred domain, gain a full bar of grey health, 45-55-65% damage reduction, and max fury. While in the kindred domain, enemies appear as wolf and allies as lamb. Attacking wolves functions normally to attacking enemy champions, while attacking lambs breaks your rage and ends the ult early. Slaying a wolf ends the ult and turns any grey health remaining into regular health. After use, the ability is locked - only recalling or death allows for it to proc again. I’m not quite sure how to put into words the fight with kindred. Particularly when trynd slashes through lamb’s bow. Obviously trynd cannot kill lamb because kindred is a primordial entity, arguably the strongest of any of them (the others being things like fiddlesticks the entity of fear) she is literally a god. But the moment she “dodges” is unnatural. It’s almost as though the world bent for a moment to ensure trynd’s blade wouldn’t touch lamb. His sword slows down, lamb moves in a fraction of a second with no real effort and then simply tilts her head.

It’s also an incredible visual to see what a struggle on the verge of death is like. Wolf’s relentless assault and lamb’s arrows combined very quickly remind you that from a lore perspective kindred is the absolute last thing you want to tango with

The last third of the video is my favorite. I never cared for Tryndamere in game but his ult does have a lot of cinematic potential as we see here. The way he defies death and its bringers (Kindred) creates a dynamic between those characters that is super enticing, and Ashe coming in as his savior and giving him the support he needs also makes me want to see more of those two. I'm very much looking forward to watching Arcane Season 2 and every other part of the world Riot decides to work on cinematically. Arcane feels somewhat grounded and "sane", which worked beautifully, but there's so much Fantasy potential for the rest of Runeterra - as we see in this video - and I can't wait to see it realized.

Loved the video and you seem to understand what was going on in the last (third) battle. I can't seem to wrap my head around it. He fought of a demon, then this... spirit attacked him with bow and arrow... is this the same person who comes to his rescue in the end? Or are they two different people. It's confusing because they resemble each other.
@@davidcrossroad8181 Kindred is death which is the wolf and lamb. The person who saved him is his wife Ashe.

@@davidcrossroad8181 In the beginning you see the Guy (Tryndamere) on the ground surrounded by enemies. The Spirit with the wolf together symbolize the Death. In reality he is fighting the Enemies who surrounded him and so at the same time he is fighting Death to not die. In the game Tryndamere has an ability who makes him somewhat invincible for some seconds (Hp does not drop below 1) and this is shown with his red eyes. In the end the woman (Ashe, his Wife) who rescues him kills the last two enemies and so he does not die and the Death fades away.

2:50 야스오의 '죽음의 순간'은,
야스오가 눈을 감고 죽음을 받아들인 것을,
'늑대가 아닌, 양의 화살에 의한 죽음'으로 표현한것 같습니다.

2:57 "불사의 분노" 사용시의,
'트린다미어의 관점'을 나타낸것 같습니다.

본래라면 마땅히 찾아 왔어야할 '죽음의 순간 - 킨드레드'에,
트린이 어떻게 싸워 이겨내는지 보여주는 것을 통해,

트린이 '죽음을 물리적으로 극복한 과정'이,
사실은 '죽음을 심상에서부터 극복한 과정과 일치한다는 점'을 잘 묘사한것 같습니다.

3:29의 킨드의 모습은,
'어떻게 마땅히 찾아왔어야 할 죽음의 순간을 거부할 수 있는지' 의아해 하는것 같습니다.
여기에서 보면 트린의 운명에는 무언가 남다른게 있는것 같습니다.

애쉬의 화살이 등장함과 함께,
킨드레드가 활을 내리는 장면은,

애쉬의 도움으로 인해서,
다시 '죽음의 순간'이 트린다미어에게서 떠났다는것을 알고,
'아직은 때가 아니라고 판단하는 모습'을 표현 하는것 같네요.

그와 동시에 나오는 노래의 가사가, '나는 아직 여기에 있다'라는 점에서,
이 시대의 우리가 어떻게 존재하고 있는지를,
게임 캐릭터를 통해 표현 하는것 같습니다.

Tryn sees Kindred because he would die if he kept fighting and we see Tryn fighting the surrounding enemies until there are only two enemies left, and when she shoots 2 arrow, Kindred knew that Tryn was no longer dangerous, so he lowered her bow and disappeared.

처음 장면 : 케일, 모르가나가 아트록스 상대하지만 둘이서 역부족.

모르가나는 검을 다시 잡지 않고 금지된 타락마법(?)으로 착지한 아트록스한테 속박[R]을 걸고 아트록스가 부수려하자 힘을 더 개방하면서(눈가의 검은 무늬가 더 펼쳐짐) 저지.

케일은 금지된 마법을 쓰는 모르가나를 못마땅하게 여기면서도 앞의 아트록스를 잡는게 우선이니 언니인 모르가나가 떨어뜨린 검을 잡고(쌍검) 승천하여(날개가 11렙 케일마냥 빛남) 아트록스에게 화염파를 날림.(스텍 안쌓아도 바로 화염파가 나오는 16렙 케일)



중간 장면 : 시정잡배가 소녀 잡으려고 다가옴.

삿갓 쓴 영감님이 그 사이를 막음.

대나무 봉으로 뚜쉬따쉬(이때까진 잭스인가..? 싶었음)

러브샷으로 영감님과 시정잡배 둘 다 밀려나고 영감님은 무기로 쓰던 대나무 봉이 부숴짐.

앞서 밀려나며 상대가 떨어뜨린 칼을 잡고 삿갓을 벗음.

짜잔 그 영감님은 사실 늙은 야스오였답니다.

바람술사답게 칼에 바람의 힘을 깃들여 넣고 반대손에도 바람의 힘을 꺼냄.

시정잡배들 쫄아서 런.

화살이 날라오는데 야스오가 바람장벽을 켜서 막음.[W]

접근하면서 질풍검[W]

그리고 이어서 강철 폭풍[Q]



마지막 장면 : 트린다미어가 누워있음.

죽음을 감지하고 킨드레드(양과 늑대)가 목숨을 걷으러 접근함.

트린은 불사의 분노[R]을 써서 발악함.

늑대가 트린과 근접전을 하며 시선을 끌고 양은 조용히 트린의 숨통을 끊으려 활 시위를 당김.

그런데 갑자기 뒤에서 많이 본 화살 두개가 날아옴.

La Unión Europea

El 12 de diciembre de 2013, el Parlamento Europeo aprobó una resolución que "expresa su profunda preocupación por los informes persistentes y creíbles de sustracción sistemática de órganos avalada por el Estado a prisioneros de conciencia sin consentimiento en la República Popular China, incluido un gran número de practicantes de Falun Dafa encarcelados por sus creencias religiosas, así como de miembros de otros grupos religiosos y étnicos minoritarios". La resolución pedía al PCCh que liberara inmediatamente a todos los presos de conciencia. También se recomendó que se llevara a cabo una investigación exhaustiva y transparente de tales comportamientos inmorales.

La Convención contra el Tráfico de Órganos Humanos también fue adoptada por el Comité Europeo de ministros el 9 de julio de 2014. Prohibió el comercio ilegal transnacional de órganos y pidió a sus países miembros que detuvieran tales crímenes.

Esta convención está en vigor en los cinco primeros estados que hasta ahora la han ratificado: Albania, República Checa, Malta, República de Moldavia y Noruega el 1 de marzo de 2018. Otros 17 países también firmaron la convención, entre ellos Bélgica, Grecia, Italia, Irlanda y Letonia.

En abril de 2019, Bélgica aprobó un nuevo proyecto de ley que penaliza todas las actividades relacionadas con la compra y venta de órganos humanos para uso comercial.

Tryndamere did not fight against Kindred. The Kindred in front of Tryndamere is a representation of death approaching Tryndamere, taking the form of a lamb and a wolf. If Tryndamere had fought Kindred, where would the enemies who were targeting Tryndamere have gone? If Tryndamere had defeated them, where would their bodies be? Where did the last appearing enemy come from? Why did Ashe shoot an arrow at the enemy lurking behind Tryndamere, not at Kindred?

Everything makes sense if we consider the enemies that initially appeared as Kindred. As Tryndamere is surrounded by enemies and death approaches, Kindred, the embodiment of death itself, appears. The lamb and wolf attack Tryndamere to harvest his death, but in reality, this is the attack of the initial enemies. Tryndamere fights against death to not succumb, but couldn't overcome it. The lamb aims its bow to harvest Tryndamere's death. However, suddenly the lamb lowers its bow. Simultaneously, the silhouette of a woman appears behind the lamb, and she shoots an arrow at the enemies behind Tryndamere. A wonderful symmetry is created with Kindred aiming the bow at Tryndamere to harvest death and Ashe aiming to save him from death.

I really like the cinematic, all of the highly detailed animations are nice to watch. All of this comes from a place of passion not hate, but I feel like the it fell short in some areas like:

Overall intensity of the whole video was lacking, this song screams defiance but it leaves you wanting more. I know they can evoke that feeling of "not giving up no matter what it costs" I saw it in The Call with Sejuani and Panth.

Old Yassuos fight with the bandits, his blade looks like it has no power behind it and people just ragdoll out of the way. I have seen them do better in Awaken when Riven fought in the Noxian arena.


Then when Morgana brings out her true power it does go very well with the music, but her animation of summoning the chains is not as intense as I would like. She only uses one hand to stop Aatrox who is a behemoth and her eyes dont go full purple and you can barely hear her scream over the music as she is maintaining the chains. I feel like a half a second more on Morg as she is casting the chains and bring that scream into the foreground would be better.

Then Kayle, when she ascends, they could have done it a shot in sync with the last three drum beats and have her swords light up bum*, close up on her intense face and glowing eyes *bum and her attack bum and let the scene breathe for a sec.

And lastly the Trynd and Kindred scene which was very good and a fantastic portray of both the char. on screen. But It would give more stakes if Trynd showed some signs of injury while combating The Wolf (he does have a claw mark on his one piece of armor on his shoulder), maybe an arrow from Lamb barely grazes him and he starts to panic so he rages, slashes that portray that he is fighting people and finally a missed opportunity that after a tussle with the Wolf, Trynd loses sight of him as he reappears behind him trying to pounce on him as Trynd looks towards Kindred reading her arrow but ultimately lowers her bow, as two frozen arrows pierce the veil and strike into the Wolf a.k.a the last two enemies.

In conclusion I still like the cinematic, but these are just some of the things in my opinion that could have been done differently.

​@@ProficientFace For those of you asking, their different approaches to justice caused a rift between them to the point they fought each other above the skies of the Demacia of old, which inadvertently caused the death of their father which is when Morgana cursed her celestial powers and saw them as a burden. She tried everything to cut or tear her wings off but never managed, so she chose instead to bind them with steel chains and walk along mortals. I think the cinematic is showing this symbolically by having Morgana cast down her mothers sword and not using her wings.

As for their different approaches to justice, Kayle's is obviously retributive justice meaning that she prefers to smite wrongdoers without a second thought. Morgana represents restorative justice, which means she prefers to try reconcile with wrongdoers and aid them, but still punish them; her chains are the main instruments of this as they cause the target to feel the pain of their sins intensely.

Dignitaries Condemn the CCP’s Forced Organ Harvesting
During the opening ceremony, Ishibashi Rintaro, a member of the House of Representatives of the National Assembly and the deputy representative of the All-Japan Local Assembly of the SMG Network (Stop Medical Genocide--Society for the Study of Organ Transplantation in China), delivered an opening speech as the sponsor of the exhibition.

Mr. Ishibashi said that the purpose of this poster exhibition was to stop the ongoing organ harvesting and transplantation crimes in China. He said the primary victims are Falun Dafa practitioners, Uyghurs, Tibetans and other groups. The CCP treats them like criminals, and harvest their organs while they are alive.

“We SMG will never allow such a thing to happen,” said Mr. Ishibashi. “But the problem at present is that although the CCP’s human rights violations have become a matter of great concern, in Japan, many people still don’t have enough opportunities to know. This poster exhibition is of fundamental significance, and lets many Japanese understand the facts of live organ harvesting (by the CCP).”

He said that another purpose was to urge the Japanese government to enact laws on overseas transplants as soon as possible. It was also important to raise awareness of this issue in the medical community and the Ministry of Health, Labor and Welfare.

Councilor Takehara Tetsu, member of Hiroshima Prefecture Assembly, said in his speech, that he would share the truth with everyone. “After viewing these artworks, my heart is very heavy, and I am more aware of our great responsibility. I think this is an opportunity for me to feel the weight of my responsibility, and I feel this from these works today,” Mr. Takehara said.

Councilor Ochiumi Naoya, member of Higashi-hiroshima City Assembly, said in his speech that he was shocked when he saw the wound represented by the currency symbol on the poster, “As a Japanese, I didn’t know about this (that the CCP harvests organs from living Falun Dafa practitioners). I hope that through the poster exhibition, more people will know about this matter.”

@@AwkwardDreamer No problem! And just for some more background context, Tryndamere is known for basically being unkillable (his ult in the game is basically undying rage and his eyes turn red and he refuses to die from any damage for a time) and Kindred is the spirit duo of death essentially, Lamb is the archer whos death is quick and peaceful (meaning you accept death) Wolfs death is like this cinematic; it's brual, a hunt, a thrashing and gnawing ordeal (meaning you are running from or trying to refuse death, which typically for the average being is out of your control) so when these two opposites clash it's a spectacle to watch. That's what I find so good about the head tilt from Kindred because Tryndamere isn't just defending himself or trying to stop death he actually goes on the offensive and basically tries attacking death to prolong his own life since he refuses to die which would be very uncommon and intriguing to come across as the spirit of death. Very well written and portrayed here.

I love Kindred. I've loved them since release. Their lore, their interactions, their design, their music. Fantastic. They are so interesting as a manifestation of death, and I love playing them. Seeing them come to life in an animation of this quality is fantastic. Wolf looks divine and intimidating, Lamb's mannerisms are so great with their little head tilt, and seeing them outlined in the other scenes is also wonderful, showing they are at each death (seeing Wolf's eyes in the treeline made me absolutely giddy). And yet, despite this, them showing up was not the single greatest shock to me. No, during this cinematic, there was one singular moment that made me actually involuntarily speak up out of surprise. And those words were "Ashe has PANTS!!!" God bless, we've waited for this day for so long.

Siedem dni minęło od kiedy opuściliśmy port Enroth. Niewolnicy, których uwolniliśmy podczas potyczki z flotą Regan mówią o dziwnych pogłoskach dochodzących z Erathii. Podejrzewam, że ich opowieści mogą mieć w sobie ziarno prawdy. Na razie jednak muszę na własne oczy zobaczyć co wydarzyło się w królestwie mego ojca.
Fale oceanu pochowały wielu z tych, którzy polegli na jego brzegu ale dymiące ruiny Cloudfire powitały nas widokiem śmierci i zniszczenia. Nikt nie przeżył, pobojowisko powiedziało mi jednak wystarczająco wiele o rozegranej tu bitwie. Pomimo ogromu zniszczeń obecność minotaurów na polu bitwy sugerowała napad złaknionej łupów bandy ale oddziały, które dokonały takiego zniszczenia musiały być dobrze wyćwiczone i dowodzone silną ręką.
Winnymi pogromu musieli być władcy podziemi. Widać iż garnizon zamku spodziewał się ataku a pomimo tego został bezlitośnie wybity do ostatniego żołnierza. Wszystkie popełnione tu okrucieństwa napełniły moje serce gniewem. Sztandar Erathii musi wzbudzać respekt i strach wrogów, nikt nie może go bezkarnie poniewierać. Myślę o moim ukochanym Rolandzie i synu Nikolaju. Na jak długo będę zmuszona ich opuścić. Mój obowiązek jest jednak oczywisty. Królestwo mego ojca musi przetrwać. Erathia nigdy nie zostanie rzucona na kolana.

You can see that his eyes glows only when he starts the intention of attacking on kindred.
He passes the death and strikes kindred. Kindred evades with a backflip and you can see on her head movement (she rolls her head on the side)that shes confused. Because she realises that this mans time hasnt come yet so she doesnt fire the last shot while ashe comes to resque.
Also the fact that first wolf attack was just a distraction wolf didnt want to attack he just leaped over tryn so kindred fires the first shot. The pact between kindred and death is kindred collects those who are going to die but if they refuse its wolfs prey now. Tryn doesnt want to die so he refuses the first arrow. Then wolf attacks and you can see kindred waiting with an arrow in hand she doesnt fire. Only when tryn attacks kindred she fires another arrow which tryn again refuses so he punches the arrow dodging it and then screaming.
So much detailing lore wise just within 10 seconds. Man I wish the game was this fun and fulfilling aswell..

This Cinematic is a materclass in storytelling. That Tryndomere/Kindred scene is an simply amazing. So well thought out. Trynd isn't actually fighting Kindred so much as fighting the ring of soldiers around him shown in the opening scene - the kindred/trynd fight is more symbollic of death being there to reap him. Then when Ashe comes she is fighting off the soldiers (notice how she doesn't even notice kindred/her arrows go right by?) 'aka' the immenent source of death, and so with no threat on trynds life any longer kindred no longer has a need to be there and reap him, Wolf and Lamb are gone. But it is trynds undying will that gets him through the fight long enough to prevail until Ash arrives. Again that's not just good cinemetography that's good writing and storytelling/building a universal lore.

Then there is the morgana/atrox/kayle fight. I'm not super familiar with their whole lore, but just in that few seconds it's like Morgana is almost 'falling' as an angel and pullihng out her dark powers to save her sister, because she doesn't do the whole chain enegery stuff until Kayle is thrown against the wall and is in mortal peril. It gives a lot of depth into understanding a characters motivation to sometimes the 'fall from grace', and shows that motivations (well written motivations) are not just 'bad guy/good guy' but are fraught with emotional drive. The symbolism of her dropping her sword and dropping her helmet to draw on dark chains is very cool. And the look from Kayle to Morg as kayle walks by is excellently animated. very small things that make a difference to the 'feel' from the viewer.

I think the only problem with the whole trailer is that no way some random raider guy would get that kick off on Yas.

Well done Rito and more importantly the individual people who made this product. Great story in just a few minutes. Happy 2024 people.

Conflicting feelings.
On the one hand, the story of Tryndamere and Ash here is perhaps the best of all time in Riot cinematics. Emotions, combat, lore component - everything is beyond praise.
On the other hand, everything else looks like it was added later just to stretch out the time. Kayle and Morgana's fight with Aatrox is just getting up to speed and is already over. Yasuo's story is the same.
And most importantly, there is no sense of lore behind it, everything happens as if in a vacuum. There is no sense of stakes, no sense that this is all part of something bigger, some epic story. The plot of Tryndamere and Ash works without context - a warrior fights for his life and receives help from his beloved. The remaining stories, however, are much weaker without the world behind them.
Subjectively, I’ll also add that I didn’t like the choice of music, although in The Call and Awaken I was delighted with the accompanying compositions.
However, for my taste, this is one of the three best cinematics for the League of Legends, right after The Call and Awaken. Despite all the obvious flaws, Tryndamere and Ash's scene is the best we've seen, and it steals the show.

After watching this several times I can safely say this is the best cinematic yet. It perfectly wraps up the concept of fighting death against all odds, using the figure of Kindred to represent this concept at every turn:

At the very beginning, Tryndamere glimpses the silhouette of Lamb, foreshadowing their fight.

In the flames of Kayle's attacks, the same silhouette appears, which I doubt represents Aatrox's death, as he's immortal, so it's maybe part of the transition.

At the end of Yasuo's fight, the eyes of Wolf appear in the treeline of the background, representing his non-acceptance of death.

My favorite sequence of all of this, which almost made me tear up due to the utter surprise, was Ashe's appearance, who, with the lyrics, almost felt as if she was the one saying "I'm still here" to Tryndamere.
I also just realized the intro "Tomorrow is a hope, never a promise" is Lamb's voice. I really didn't see it coming the first time.

After watching this several times I can safely say this is the best cinematic yet. It perfectly wraps up the concept of fighting death against all odds, using the figure of Kindred to represent this concept at every turn:

At the very beginning, Tryndamere glimpses the silhouette of Lamb, foreshadowing their fight.

In the flames of Kayle's attacks, the same silhouette appears, which I doubt represents Aatrox's death, as he's immortal, so it's maybe part of the transition.

At the end of Yasuo's fight, the eyes of Wolf appear in the treeline of the background, representing his non-acceptance of death, and despite of that, he's hit with an arrow of Lamb at the end.

My favorite sequence of all of this, which almost made me tear up due to the utter surprise, was Ashe's appearance, who, with the lyrics, almost felt as if she was the one saying "I'm still here" to Tryndamere.

⚠Unpopular opinion Warning⚠: I'm seeing everyone praise this so much but honestly I still think it hits short in comparison to 2020-2022 cinematics. There was some really cool moments and the whole consistent metaphor of death with Kindred was well thought out. But the actual storylines in comparison with previous ones were meh and the scenes just seemed to climax and move on which made for a really disjointed full video. In previous cinematics all the plots/storylines came to a climax towards the end and this works much better than just cutting and restarting a new scene on each verse.

I would like to see if they used the same creative agencies they did in 2020-2022 and if not i would suggest they go back to them.

O olhar de desdem da Kayle para Morgana quando ela conjura a magia dela pra mim doeu até a alma. A Morgana literalmente usando a alma dela pra prender o Atroox, sofrendo, e a Kayle fria como gelo. Dá pra entender bem a relação delas ai.

Não, você ta entendendo errado a relação delas, e provavelmente nunca as entendeu.
Espero que agora que finalmente as duas estão sendo a "Justiça" como aparenta o trailer, você comece a entender, que a mensagem das duas, é que elas nunca deveriam ter se separado, e as duas levou do jeito errado sua dor.
A Kayle não é tão criminosa como vocês printam, e morgana não é tão heroina como printam. Mas o fato que as duas se gostam ao ponto que tentaram afastar a dor cada uma de um jeito errado, e inclusive se olhar bem as falas dela, a de morte de kayle, seu último pedido é vê sua irmã.
E isso que to falando acima não é só minha interpretação, escritor já falou que a historia das duas, é que separadas são erradas, e juntas são a justiça.

Les voy a dar un poco de contexto para que entiendan la pelea de trynda con kindred y para que vean porque es tan espectacular la última secuencia:

Kindred es la muerte?

No, kindred es la representación previa a la muerte. La muerte como tal es otro ser que llega cuando kindred determina como muere un ser (violento o piadoso)

Trynda ataca a la oveja pero no al lobo, del lobo solo se defiende:

-la oveja es la muerte por piedad o por enfermedad es decir la muerte natural. Recordemos que trynda está en el suelo en la cinemática, no sabemos cuánto tiempo lleva ahí, puede que se estuviera desangrando o tuviera una herida profunda en un órgano. La oveja dispara esperando darle fin a su vida pero trynda la ataca.

Porque el arco de La oveja se rompe?

-Porque trynda acaba de negar la muerte natural, el rompimiento del arco es simplemente la representación de "desafío a la muerte".

Kindred pudo haber muerto por la espada?

-No, kindred está en otro plano y los únicos que pueden matarlos son unos buitres que no me acuerdo cómo se llaman, pero el punto es, kindred piensa que es inmortal (pero no lo es).

Entonces entra a atacar el lobo ¿Quien es el lobo?

-El lobo es la muerte violenta involuntaria, es decir, por ejemplo, una decapitación, aplastamiento etc etc. En la vida real serían los guerreros detrás de trynda, intentando matarlo con sus hachas y espadas.

Porque la oveja no dispara mientras ataca el lobo?

-Porque no puede, ya que no es una muerte por piedad.

Porque kindred desaparece cuando llega ashe?

-porque trynda ya no está en peligro y evadió a la muerte.

І того це мало б бути частиною лора. Тобто маєм 3 різні часові частини:

1. В древності, ще до того як сестри посварились, Моргана і Кейл бились проти Атрокса та його армії фрельйордців. Невідомо хто переміг, але всі троє залишились живими.
2. В недалекому минулому, армія Атрокса напала на Триндаміра. (Або це бій проти іншого племені, уже після того як Триндамір став чоловіком Еш, бо по лору Еш і Тринда зустрілись через деякий час після знищення села Триндаміра, а не під час цього). Він напівживий б'ється буквально проти смерті в обличчі Кіндрет, доки йому на допомогу не приходить Еш.
3. В далекому майбутньому старий Ясуо б'ється проти армії наворі (?) і в результаті знищує групу загарбників, але помирає від стріли. Я так розумію, від стріли тієї ж Кіндред.

Ну і в чому прикол? Навіщо такі різні часові відрізки без контексту? Раніше, коли виходив кінематик, то випускали й якесь оповідання, котре пояснювало хоч частину цього кінематика. Зараз нічого. В чому прикол? Залишили нас з купую питань, без жодної відповіді. Окей, так, виглядає круто, але конкретика де? Де обіцяне адекватне розширення лору? Як на мене, то весь цей ролик виглядає як один суцільний трейлер до одного серіала на купу сезонів, або як трейлер до трьох різних фільмів.

В цілому - не задоволений. Стільки чекали, а в результаті нічого.

I love the depiction of Tryndamere fighting Kindred even though he wasn't actually fighting Kindred.
---
He was fighting those enemies at the start of the cinematic.
It was like a Metaphor or just a Creative Hallucination that depicts Tryndamere being on the verge of Death and is fighting Death itself refusing to die.
His rage drowned him making him see himself as fighting Death but seeing Ashe helped calm him down to realize that he is not meant to die yet and that allowed him to come back to his senses when he saw the arrows and Ashe at the end.

It's more likely that lore-wise Kindred actually showed up there but either way it still serves it's purpose whether it was metaphorical or literal, Death's presence was still in there.

Amazing. Less popular characters, but set in scene so beautifully. I love the characterisation in every part, the way Morgana plummets from the light skies, the disdain in Kayle's eyes, the way Kindred are neither malevolent nor vincible, the blind fury of Aatrox.
I gasped when Lamb lowered their bow as Ashe's arrows whizz past, the way Kindred doesn't take lives out of malevolence, and as Tryndamere is saved, it is not against them. The way Kindred are incorporeal, too much so, but it just makes sense because they are inevitable, invincible, and yet not malevolent.
I love this trailer, and if it's any indication of RIOT's focus on the lore that they announced, we are in for some great pieces.

When she eventually comes to save him, he lays his eyes on her, he is safe with her (Kindred fades as the threat of death is gone) being shown by his red raging eyes returning to normal color (exits his ult).
(Little detail: In this fight Wolf is the primary aggressor as Trynda isn't accepting death)

With the Aatrox vs Morgana and Kayle fight- it looks like they were defending Demacia during it's early days (when they were venerated as it's winged protectors)
Morgana's wings become bound and she lays on the ground when she chains Aatrox
Kayle on the other hand gets up later and delivers her judgement (unlike her sister her wings ablaze) both showing their lore, game play and views on justice!
